 Tips & tricks
 















 
 
 

 
 
 
 




 
 
 
 The Richmond is easy-care! 
 
 

 
 
 
 - Air the tent after every use and let it dry before you pack it away. If the weather makes this impossible, remove it from the pack sack as soon as possible and dry thoroughly. This will prevent mildew stains, mould, discolouration or odours and will maintain its functionality.
 
 

 
 
 
 - Small stains can be wiped off carefully with a damp cloth. Do not use any harsh cleaning products and do not rub too aggressively on the fabric otherwise you might damage the waterproofing
 
 

 
 
 
 - Zips can be sprayed with silicon so they are easier to move if applicable
 
 

 
 
 
 - Use the sturdy, separate pack bags for the poles and the tent pegs. This will protect the sensitive tent fabric from damage if you store the entire tent accessories in the large pack sack
 
 

 
 
 
 Storage
 
 

 
 
 
 Thanks to the very small pack size, the tent can easily be stored in a small item of luggage and at home. Please ensure that the tent is packed away when it is dry and store it in a clean, dry place.
 
 

 
 
 
 Construction / dismantling
 
 

 
 
 
 Choose your tent pitch carefully. Sharp stones can damage the fabric. A ground sheet will protect the floor from damage and dirt. Avoid erecting the tent in a hollow. Rain water can collect there, which could penetrate into the tent in the worst case scenario. 
 
 

 
 
 
 If there is a strong wind, you should fasten the tent with additional ropes. This will distribute the tensile load and protect the seams.
 
 

 
 
 
 It is easy to pitch and provides secure shelter for the night:
 
 

 
 
 
 - Pull the tent carefully out of the pack sack and spread it out
 
 

 
 
 
 - Then push the tent poles that have been inserted into each other through the hooks envisaged for this and the upper pole stirrup and push the ends of the poles into the eyelets on the floor
 
 

 
 
 
 - Fix the corner points of the tent floor with the tent pegs supplied
 
 

 
 
 
 - Throw over the external tent and also fasten it down with tent pegs
 
 

 
 
 
 - Now pull the tent apart with the guy ropes and fasten it to the floor with more tent pegs
